    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Molly, I can tell you haven&#39;t lost your sense of humor no matter how exhausted you feel. That&#39;s good! And yes, just like with a baby, (and kids later on) you can&#39;t imagine your life without them/the restaurant and you love it so althought it/they demand so much of your time and energy, and at the same time, it/they give you so much in return.<br />But, unlike kids, a restaurant doesn&#39;t hold your career back üôÇ<br />Sorry to use this analogy again. But it just seems so much like family indeed when you own and run your own business and you put your heart and soul into it.<br />Hope to visit Delancey again soon. Nurit</p>
    </div>

