    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/01493708300940204826" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Molly</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2009/09/what-i-do-now/#comment-19668"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2009-10-01T17:06:26-04:00">Thursday, October 1, 2009 at 5:06 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Cookie Baker Lynn and Katherine, I&#39;m so sorry for the confusion!  A single batch of this crumble should be made in a 9-inch round pie plate.  (See the last sentence of the 2nd paragraph of the instructions, the sentence that begins &#8220;Arrange the plums&#8230;.&#8221;)  If you triple the recipe, though, you should make it in a 9 x 13.</p>
    </div>

